<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>io.github.user.WayfinderVoice</id>
  
  <name>Wayfinder Voice</name>
  <summary>Local voice dictation using whisper.cpp</summary>
  
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>
  
  <developer id="io.github.user">
    <name>Wayfinder Voice Developer</name>
  </developer>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Wayfinder Voice is a local voice dictation application for Linux. Press a hotkey, 
      speak, and your words are typed wherever your cursor is. All processing happens 
      on your machine using whisper.cpp — your voice never leaves your computer.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>100% Local &amp; Private — No cloud services, no data collection</li>
      <li>Hotkey Triggered — Press a key to start/stop recording</li>
      <li>Wayland &amp; X11 Support — Works on modern Linux desktops</li>
      <li>System Tray Integration — Runs quietly in the background</li>
      <li>Multiple Whisper Models — Choose speed vs accuracy (tiny → large)</li>
      <li>Configurable Typing Speed — Instant paste or simulated typing</li>
      <li>Beautiful Dark Theme — Premium UI inspired by Wayfinder OS</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Perfect for writing emails, documents, code comments, chat messages, or any 
      situation where speaking is faster than typing.
    </p>
  </description>
  
